{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/split-screens-vim","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"45b6d5a1-1fd8-53bc-9844-a1365692670b","html":"<p>Have you ever found yourself going through a long file in <code class=\"language-text\">vim</code> and wishing you could split your screen?  Perhaps you want to make some comparison with a chunk at the top of file with something in the middle.  With a few keystrokes you can do exactly that.</p>\n<h2 id=\"split-horizontally\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#split-horizontally\" aria-label=\"split horizontally permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Split Horizontally</h2>\n<p><img src=\"/ef52bc2cbcb9ed60012c065c119c8eaf/vim-split-screen-h.gif\" alt=\"Horizontal Screen Split\"></p>\n<p>To split the screen horizontally:\na.) Hit <code class=\"language-text\">CTRL</code> + <code class=\"language-text\">w</code>\nb.) and then <code class=\"language-text\">s</code>.</p>\n<p>If you want to navigate between the screen:\na.) Hit <code class=\"language-text\">CTRL</code> + <code class=\"language-text\">w</code>\nb.) and then <code class=\"language-text\">w</code>.  </p>\n<p>To exit out of one of the screen:\na.) Go into command mode (i.e. hit <code class=\"language-text\">ESC</code>)\nb.) and quit as usual: <code class=\"language-text\">:q</code>. </p>\n<h2 id=\"split-vertically\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#split-vertically\" aria-label=\"split vertically permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Split Vertically</h2>\n<p><img src=\"/badf531a9a9a6e374af017f962920f46/vim-split-screen-v.gif\" alt=\"Vertical Screen Split\"></p>\n<p>To split the screen vertically, much like splitting horizontally:\na.) Start by hitting <code class=\"language-text\">CTRL</code> + <code class=\"language-text\">w</code>\nb.) but then hit <code class=\"language-text\">v</code> (instead of <code class=\"language-text\">s</code>).  </p>\n<p>Navigating between the split screens is the same (<code class=\"language-text\">CTRL</code> + <code class=\"language-text\">w</code> + <code class=\"language-text\">w</code>). </p>\n<p>Though horizontal splitting works great.  I find vertical splitting to be the most useful.</p>\n<h2 id=\"combine-both\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#combine-both\" aria-label=\"combine both permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Combine Both</h2>\n<p><img src=\"/42a2c3df11873da2c95bea0a88b5ef2a/vim-split-screen-b.gif\" alt=\"Vertical and Horizontal Screen Split\"></p>\n<p>Why choose?  It is possible to combine both horizontal and vertical screen splitting as well.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/split-screens-vim","tagSlugs":["/tag/vi/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-10-14","description":"Have you ever found yourself going through a long file in `vim` and wishing you could split your screen? tags: vim,","tags":["vi"],"title":"How to Split Screens in vim","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/split-screens-vim"}}}